SCOPE & STOP Hormones Analysis 24 February 2023 Overview This page contains analysis results for SCOPE and STOP Hormones. Absorbance Concentrations: Standard curves

1 Standard Curves This section contains standard curves fitted for Prolactin, HPL, and GH2. GH2 Plate 22 (28-2-22) omitted due to invalid standard curve. Inter-assay CV for Prolactin and HPL higher than recommended 15%. According to the protocols, the following methods were used for curve fitting: - Prolactin: Quadratic - HPL: 4-parameter Logistic - GH2: non-linear splines

2 Plate Effect This section explores the Plate effect on hormone levels. 28 Hormone Models - Outcomes: Prolactin, hPL, GH2 (all outcomes log-transformed) - Independent variables: Study, f39_gdm_new, BMI, Ethnicity (Caucasian/non-Caucasian), smoking (yes/no), GA at sampling - Model fitted: LME model       log(hormones) ~ Study + f39_gdm_new + BMI + Ethnicity + Smoking + GA at sampling + Study:GDM       Random intercepts for Study ID and Plate #outc_ls <- c("Prolactin","HPL","GH2") outc_ls <- hormone_var outc2 <- preg_out # fit LME fit_ls <- lapply(outc_ls,function(outc){ fit_eq <- as.formula(paste0("log(",outc,")~ Study + ",outc2," + BMI + Ethnicity_cauc + f10c_any_cig_1st_vst + GA_samp + Study*",outc2," + (1|Study.ID) + (1|Assay.",outc,")")) fit <- eval(bquote(lmer(.(fit_eq),data=dat_run))) return(fit)}) names(fit_ls) <- outc_ls # Type III SS anova_ls <- lapply(fit_ls,Anova,type="III")
